            <title>[SPARK-18457] ORC and other columnar formats using HiveShim read all columns when doing a simple count</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-18457</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Doing a `select count&lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/star_yellow.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; from a_orc_table` reads all columns and thus is slower than a query selecting one like `select count(a_column) from a_orc_table`. Data read can be seen in the UI (appears to only be accurate for Hadoop 2.5+ based on comment in FileScanRDD.scala line 80).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will create a PR shortly.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Hadoop 2.7.0&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
